reviews: The staff at the hotel was amazing and friendly. They all were a great help and made us feel welcome at all times. At no point did I feel like they were not at their best. Would love to come back to stay in the future.

Top notch! It's a small boutique hotel but very nice and clean. We only had breakfast at the restaurant but I'm sure it's also good for lunch and dinner. There's a small bar on the rooftop that has a great view of Paris and the Eiffel Tower. Rooms are nice, bathroom is larger than many in Europe and has a huge shower. The location can't really get any better. It's on a side street right off Champs-Elysees, easy to walk almost anywhere.

The accommodation was perfect and the safe were so lovely and kind. I greatly enjoyed myself and I highly recommend everything about it. Thank you so much for all your kindness and help. It was above our expectations and we will definitely be back. Nicholas Stankiewicz

Such a lovely boutique hotel in the best part of Paris. Easy walking distance to shopping and the main attractions
The staff are so helpful and friendly, the rooms are spacious, quiet and have comfy beds and great amenities.
We had an excellent stay here and can’t wait to come back

We had a fabulous time in Paris thanks to the very kind and informative staff at the hotel. They gave us excellent recommendations and made reservations for dining and tours. Most of all, we loved our driver Marouan! Not only did he make himself available to drive us, he looked after our every need. He is charming, knowledgeable and a complete delight.

Having our wedding at Hotel Marignan was the best decision we made. Everything from the view to the hotel far exceeded our expectations, but it was Cecile and the rest of the staff that made it truly memorable. They put us at ease and helped ensure that our special day went just the way we wanted. We could not have asked for a better day and a big part of that is due to the staff at Hotel Marignan

We had the most amazing time at the Hotel Marignan!! We stayed there for a total of 5 nights and I prepared surprises for my husband with the hotels help. Everyone was so incredibly kind and helpful all the time. And you can’t beat the view from the rooms!!!! We stayed at Terrace Suite and Suite Marignan. Absolutely the BEST experience we have had!! Recommend it 1.000%!!!!

The staff provided the best service we’ve ever received. Rooms were gorgeous, cozy and clean. Restaurant and bar were phenomenal.

The property is within walking distance to several restaurants and cafes, but a bit of a drive to most major attractions. However, would absolutely stay here again based on the service and the property.

We had a great stay at the Hotel Marignan Champs Elysee. Very nice room but it was the service that really made it special. Nothing was too much trouble from transfers to restaurant recommendations. Our friends were celebrating a special birthday and they gave them a beautiful cake with plates for 4 knowing we were also staying at the same hotel. Very thoughtful.

They ruined my brand new 3k LV luggage! I tried calling and emailing them with no reply or answer. I am so disappointed to stay at this hotel. They also had no AC and the beds are small and uncomfortable.

The staffs were very attentive. My fiancé and I were there to celebrate my birthday. Hotel surprised us with Happy Birthday balloons, a cake and a bottle of red wine. It was a really nice touch. The room was comfortable, and the breakfast was very good.

Overall, WONDERFUL stay! We'll definitely be back.

The location of this hotel is everything! Definitely recommend paying for an Eiffel Tower room, as the view is incredible day and night. Staff are super friendly and couldn’t do enough for you, we will definitely be back to stay on our next trip to Paris.

This hotel and staff were lovely. They were extremely accommodating and provided the highest level of service. They were able to arrange an in home visit from a doctor when we needed it, put a rose that we had lying around in a vase with water, and were there for everything we needed throughout our stay. Would highly recommend!

We were very disappointed to find out that the restaurant (Limon) was closed. This was one of the key factors in our decision to stay at the Marignan. There was no mention whatsoever, whether on the website or upon our arrival, so we had to find out for ourselves.

This also meant that the breakfast choice was very limited and served in one of the reception areas. One morning it was served in one of the 1st floor rooms!

All of that said, the location is excellent, our room was very comfortable and the service from the hotel staff (esp Alexei & Tahar) very good.

Not 5 star (in my opinion).

This hotel made our family’s first trip to Europe that much more special. The concierge was incredibly helpful arranging experiences well before our arrival. The staff were so friendly and helpful. The room was beautiful and comfortable. Will recommend to all that travel to Paris in the future!

Hotel Marignon was a very comfy & homey stay for us. While it has all the 5-star quality of amenities & well-appointed bathroom & walk-in closet, it feels more like our own apartment rather than a hotel suite. We also booked the cinema & enjoyed a great movie during our stay. Very convenient location & an overall great value.

Fantastic location, hotel, and staff going above and beyond to make their guests happy. Recommended for paris. Rooms are great with excellent views and high ceilings. Location can’t be any better in my opinion.

Best hotel we’ve ever been in Paris! It was such a memorable trip. From the kindness of the staff to the perfect location. Our suite had the most beautiful terrace with the iconic view of the Eiffel Tower. They put up a romantic set and made it even more beautiful! We had dinner at the hotel and the food was 5 stars. Can only say good things about this hotel! Truly recommend it if you’re staying in Paris!

This has been our third stay in the hotel since 2013 and while we still enjoyed it, we could see that the rooms and facilities are getting a bit old and a renovation would be very great !
The breakfast is excellent and provides a lot of choices.
The staff is very nice and helpful.
On the first day, there were some wifi connection issues on our floor and they solved the issues in few hours. As a nice compensation gesture, they offered us a free ride to our restaurant with one of the hotel cars.
We will be back soon!

This hotel exceeded expectations. We booked a junior suite which had a lovely balcony with views of the Eiffel Tower. The staff were really attentive and could not be more helpful. Without prompting they organised balloons a cake and a gift for my daughter's birthday, it was a really classy touch

I cannot thank the staff enough for making such a memorable anniversary trip. They went above and beyond to make us feel special. Their attention to little details were truly amazing. Their concierge services got us tickets to the museums, so we skipped the huge lines. They also made dinner reservation for us and recommended us great local restaurants. Our room had a beautiful view of the Eiffel tower, and was always very clean. Totally recommend this hotel if you are staying in Paris, the location is also another great plus, very centric. Nothing but the best you will find in this hotel! Again, thank you,
Roxana.

What can I say, Hotel Marignan went above and beyond for us on our stay. We had a gorgeous view of the Eiffel tower and the staff put on an unbelievable rose petal and flower display to make our long weekend even more meaningful. The staff were extremely attentive and friendly and the vibe was to notch. The facilities were all top of the range and the location was, of course, fantastic. Cannot recommend enough.

From the moment we booked 12 months ago, the staff have been amazing. Paris at New Year, what is there not to like! The Hotel, the staff, food and service is just amazing! They looked after us, made the birthday celebration amazing and could not have done any more. If you are thinking of this hotel, don’t think, just book! You will love it!

wonderful view, great location and considerate services
before and during our stay, we all felt from hotels warm-hearted greetings and services, room was spacious and clean. the location is great which is near champs-elysee and metro station. we stayed at
the suite with terrace, the view from which was so great that we can overlooking the Eiffel tower. We really enjoy our stay here.

I could say that we are very frequent travelers for the las 20 years and this staying at Morignan was probably the best experience; the people working at this hotel are exceptional from the lady that makes the room to the people at the front door , front desk and restaurant, thank you all of them for making our staying so pleasant :
Anny
Victoria
Nayeli
Jean Francoise
Ishem
Alex
Mbaye
Amed, etc
Congrats !!

We had an outstanding stay! Our room was comfortable, the hotel is close to everything and the staff was always helpful! Lucie Linardon and Laureen Agaësse did an excellent job with the 1920s themed New Year’s celebration! We watched the fireworks from the rooftop deck drinking champagne. It was so much fun! Bonne Année 2023!

The hotel and staff were the best I highly recommended this hotel, we felt like in home the view from the roof top was amazing I can imagine is summer what it will look. The staff took and extra steep to help us whit all out need and made sure they were fulfilled.

We travelled here in a multi-generational group to celebrate a milestone wedding anniversary.

We had 4 rooms in total including 2 x Premiere Rooms, 1 x Family Duplex and the Marignan Eiffel Suite.

First Impressions;
We arrived at this beautiful hotel early from our flight. Upon arrival you will notice the beautiful Christmas decorations that surrounds the entrance. The decorations continued within the lobby and little area near the bar. The hotel appeared chic and sophisticated and charming. We were delighted.

Due to our early arrival, not all the rooms were ready so we headed out to an early lunch. The door staff kindly took all our luggage and stored it safely. We were called about an hour later and told our rooms were ready.

The front desk area is small but there is further seating in front of the bar area where you can wait.

Rooms:
I had a chance to look at all the room types and found them perfectly appointed.

The premiere rooms were small but well laid out, so worked well for our solo travelers (or a couple). There was a view onto other buildings but with beautiful French architecture to look upon, so it wasn't a complaint from us. Just remember to draw the curtains, when needed.

The duplex family room, was fantastic. My kids loved this room, and were delighted by the stairs they could climb up and down. It worked so well for a family as the children could play and hang out downstairs and the upstairs sleeping space was solely for that. How can I not mention that there were two toilets which is always handy for a family. There was ample storage space downstairs so we could unpack and organise ourselves for our one night stay.

My only one issue was that the vanity in the sleeping area was a little dark/not well lit (but it was December) so it was difficult to really use it.

The Marignan Eiffel Suite was the reason we came to this hotel. We wanted to book our relatives into this gorgeous suite with stunning terrace for their anniversary. Although, I had seen every picture possible of this suite, I was still blown away by how amazing it was. There was alot of storage with a walk in wardrobe when you enter. A cosy living room is located in the center of the suite, with two sets of doors opening out onto the terrace. Then there is a master bathroom with a freestanding bath, perfectly located to take in the view. Finally a master bedroom.
The room takes full advantage of the view and we were able to go outside and take some photos as well as watch the lights later from the cosy living room.

The cleanliness of all the rooms were very high and we enjoyed the little touches the hotel had prepared - which included macaroons in each room and a teddy bear for the children. The suite had a lovely fresh flower display, cake and wine for the couple celebrating.

Location:
The location is superb. It is on a street that is perfectly located in between the Champ Elysees and Avenue Montaigne. The restaurant L'Avenue is also on the corner. A whole host of restaurants and cafes are available close by as well as shopping. We were only here for one night so it was perfect for us to get around quickly. It was winter and (minus 2 one morning) so we did get taxis to the Eiffel tower but I am sure in the summer it would be a delightful walk.

Staff:
All the staff at this hotel were exceptional. Nothing was too much trouble. They were very welcoming and helpful. We happened to be here the night of the England v France world cup game and the hotel had organised the game to be shown in the cinema room downstairs. Thank you to all the staff at this hotel during our stay.

Breakfast:
As we travel with children, we usually book breakfast with the hotel we are staying at. We had an early morning photoshoot so we were the first ones in on the Sunday. There is mix of pastries, cheeses, juices and hot breakfast. It is a small selection and all served self service. You can order coffees from the staff. The breakfast is served in the bar and as such feels quite luxurious! It is a small but perfectly adequate for the size of the hotel and has enough choice to have a lovely meal.

Final Thoughts:
We truly enjoyed our weekend at Hotel Marignan and are already thinking about coming back when it is warmer. The location and the suites are reason alone to come back however, the personal touches and staff are the aspects that made this hotel a stand out diamond for us.

Tip: we booked our stay directly with the Hotel and were given a free transfer back to the airport.

There are two lifts, one small and one slightly larger in the hotel. You may have to wait a little while during busy times.

Stayed in this hotel back in June and it was ok. Was traveling with two kids under 8, and was looking to the hotel at the last moment since the flight route and schedule changed. Arrived at hotel at midnight and was welcomed with a gufe attitude, extra charges for kid and rune twin side bed. The tone, the was to address and absolutely 0 efforts to help made me almost cry. 2k usd for 30 hours in the hotel which barely wants to say hi and bye. Once we get into the room, I saw absolutely weird and gross spots of something on the watt in bathroom. Next morning I informed the assistant manager Ulyana, who was absolutely pathetic and extremely rude. Instead of taking responsibility and taking actions to improve my experience in hotel she said they did a hide gesture to letting me stay with a kid even if I pad for him extra. For spots no one every showed up and cleaned them. The customer service, the front desk, maid service and even an assistant manager have huge issues with hospitality and professionalism. I would never recommend this hotel, stay away!

Wonderful service from the entire team. We enjoyed our stay very much. This will definitely be our choice of hotel for our next trip to Paris. Blown away by the attentive staff. Breakfast was a delight. The tiramisu rocks!

This is in a great spot. You can easily walk to L’Arc and most high-end stores. L’Avenue is also right around the corner for a quick bite. The rooms are very small as per Paris standards but the restrooms are very difficult to get in and out of — I’m talking yoga moves to open/close the door. Great value for the money and the staff is very friendly (which is hard to find in Paris.) I would definitely recommend.

Great service experience from the door man, reception and other staff members. Fast efficient service with a smile and far better than some 5 star establishments. The excellent location of the hotel is an added advantage for staying

Incredible hotel with exceptional customer service. Each staff member from the front desk, to the bar to those handling our baggage were superb, friendly and went above and beyond to make our trip memorable. Thank you. I look forward to returning soon!

Great Location, easy access to metro and Champs. very friendly and helpful staff, they went above and beyon to explain the hotel amenities and how to navigate the city. Gabe us good recommendations for restaurants. Clean and comfortable room and bed

My wife and I have stayed here 3 times. Each time, it gets better and better. From the design and ergonomics of the rooms (we've stayed in the Marignan suite, and Eiffel tower rooms), to the friendliness at the restaurant (Victoria is great), this home away from home really checks all of the boxes. Located near the Seine and off a quiet Champs Elysees side street, you can't go wrong with Marignan.

We stayed at the hotel for 3 nights for a family trip. Once the hotel staff heard we were celebrating a birthday, they sent an amazing cake to the room, with decorations and balloons.
The room was clean and comfortable, cleaning services are great. Breakfast was delicious.
The staff is incredible- everyone is so friendly and eager to help. Great location- just off the Champs Elysee. Would definitely come back here.

I just came home from Paris and our extraordinary stay in this unique and wonderful hotel. Rarely do you find such excellent quality along with professionalism under the same roof! My motto in life is “kindness, I discovered, is EVERYTHING”. Everyone in this hotel was much more than this! Thank you and we will be back!

We truly got great service throughout our stay.
From the chamber-maid to the concierge and porters though to the reception and management. In every case great service.
The location is brilliant with easy walking to the Eiffel Tower, Champs Elise and Arc de Triumph.
All in all - as good as you can get

Very good hotel. Rooms are not big, but comfortable. Breakfast it’s ok. Could be more varied. Location is very good. Close to many fashion boutiques. Rooms are clean. Reception staff is very attentive and responsive.

This hotel was so conveniently located right next to all the shopping, within a 15 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower, and less than a minute walk to a metro station. Staff were all so friendly and accommodating and the rooms were incredible! Would definitely stay here again and recommend to anyone visiting Paris

We have paid around 750€ per room per night.
The location is very good but for the rest like a medium 4 or 3 start hotel.
Nothing special.
For me the value is 400€ just for the situation. Otherwise 250€

Enjoyed our week at Hotel Marignan Champs Elysees. Lovely staff, a great location in the 8th, and a nice sized room and large bathroom. The bed was very comfortable as well. The staff was so helpful and met all our needs.

We absolutely loved our stay here! Really amazing hotel in a fantastic location - very close to the bustling Champs Elysee. Also, the service was out of this world. They were so kind and attentive throughout our short stay, and the staff couldn't have been nicer. The lounge/bar area was stunning, and it was a very chic spot to get a drink and some complimentary truffled nuts. The room was also very spacious, comfortable, and clean, and the bathroom + amenities were fantastic as well. Another nice surprise was that we had a little balcony in our room, which I was not expecting! Would love to come back to this location the next time we are in Paris!

great located, excellent service, the rooms were a bit small. The price was on the high side but for shopping and sight seeing I recommend staying there. You can basically walk to main tourist points.

The hotel is very chic, nicely decorated and updated. We stayed in one of the "family rooms". We booked a room with a king size bed and a twin size bed for 3 of us, but ended up with 2 full size beds which also worked fine. Breakfast was great and plentiful.
If I can make one recommendation it is to book the hotel directly. If you do so, the hotel pays for the taxi back to the airport. I was not able to book directly since the room we wanted did not show as available on their website.
One complaint I have is that bed linens get changed every day, towels even twice a day. I doubt that even people with deep pockets require that kind of attention. Giving attention to environment and saving water would be a great message and investment in the future.

Service was good. Place was nice. Food service was ok.
Personnel was polite.Locaion was the reason for us to get this hotel, to see Eiffel Tower from the balcony. Could come also another time. Room was nice.

This was a great stay for my wife & I. We've stayed in many hotels for work & vacation all over the world. This one of our top five hotel stay's. Great location, clean, helpful, centrally located, we walk to everything . We will be back !

Our good impression started before arriving. The concierge Jean François helped us to book the best restaurants in town prior to our arrival. This make that visit to Paris very special and memorable. All the staff is careful. The breakfast is excellent. Strongly recommend this hotel!

We enjoyed our stay at the Marignan. The rooftop terrace was beautiful with amazing views. The hotel felt very cozy and the service was outstanding, every single person went over and above to make sure everything was great. We also enjoyed the daily breakfast that was served. I would definitely recommend this hotel for its superb location and amazing service!

Finally a hotel with service to match their web site. The ENTIRE staff was kind, helpful, well trained, and very eager to accommodate any and all requests. The location is obviously a major plus, and the rooftop lounge affords a 100% full view of the Eiffel tower in the distance. They allowed us to drop off our luggage prior to check in so we could enjoy sightseeing. If I was forced to give a negative, the view from our room was ok, but the adjoining room design and quality of the amenities easily made up for that.

My two teenage daughters and I stayed at the hotel. We were received at the hotel with a warm welcome. All the service providers were courteous and pleasant. The room we stayed in was pleasant. The breakfast was limited but good and fresh every morning. The staff helped with anything needed. The rooftop was inviting, maybe you could add a few more options for snacking while sitting at the rooftop. Walking distance from the Champs-Elysées.

I do not normally review hotels but I feel compelled to promote Hotel de Marignan Champs Elysees. The level of service provided was excellent. The accommodations were excellent. The attention the staff paid to me during my solo visit to Paris was amazing and above and beyond. For example, I spoke time the concierge because I could not find a tart tartin which is a traditional French dessert. Marion, the manager, overheard the conversation and told me they would find one for me. Instead, she had the chef prepare an entire tart tartin for me and surprised me with a delivery to my suite. I was amazed, loss for words, I have never received this level of service and consideration and it’s a testament to the lengths this staff will go to make your stay unforgettable. I will ALWAYS stay at this hotel whenever I visit Paris. On a past trip to Paris I stayed at a hotel and was underwhelmed. A friend referred me to this chic, boutique, modern luxury establishment and they surpassed the excellent recommendation I received. The entire staff, from the doormen to the room service assistants to the front desk, concierge and the manager herself, Marion, personalized my stay and made it unforgettable. Additionally, the location is amazing, one half block off of the Champs Elysees strip and a block away from George V made it very convenient to enjoy the Parisian community and the best sights in town. I wish I could give 10 stars! They definitely earned them. Can’t wait to see them again.

I stayed here for two nights and thought the hotel & the staff could not have done much more to make our stay perfect.
The staff were attentive, thoughtful and courteous. The concierge was knowledgable and very helpful.
Would recommend to a friend and certainly stay again.

We didn't get a chance to stay at the hotel, this is a review of their rooftop bar. We had reservations there for Bastille Day and it was quite the experience. The rooftop is fairly intimate, only seating about 30 something people. The food was very pleasant and service was top notch. We has an amazing evening and the fireworks along with the view really sent it over the top.

This hotel is beautiful, from the rooms/terraces, to the rooftop, to the bar... we had such an amazing stay.

The staff though is what stood out the most. The entire staff was amazing, Lucie and Cecile helped me plan an engagement here, and they helped with the most specific details to make the evening brilliant and beautiful. I've never met such helpful staff, especially at such a beautiful hotel. 10/10, and the Terrace rooms are amazing.

A nice Hotel with convenient location. Not a 5 star but I would rate as 4 star. The room was nice and decent size for Paris. The included breakfast was excellent. The bar/restaurant staff were pleasant but so very slow. The rooftop bar was very nice but you had to hunt down the server. The maid service was very good. Overall I would say their rooms are over priced based on the service and amenities.

This property was conveniently located. It is a mere 3 minute walk to the Champs. The decor is really cute and the room is nice and quiet. There is a rooftop restaurant that has the most beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower. The staff was very kind and helpful. I would stay here again. 5 stars.

Our room was on the smaller side but very clean and comfortable with everything we needed! The staff could not be friendlier or more helpful; from the front desk guys to the doorman to the waitstaff. Literally one block off the best two shopping districts around, and the lovely little rooftop lounge has amazing views of the Eiffel Tower! Would absolutely stay here again.

We loved this hotel. Great location and fabulous staff! We had a suite and it was lovely. The rooftop bar was really great, but the Staff was truly the best. They were very helpful and attentive to our needs. I would definitely go back!

Incredible stay at the beautiful Hotel Marignan. A hotel that caters for everyone, a modern exterior, rooms with a gorgeous view of Paris and delicious French food! The staff were so lovely and we’re so welcoming and helpful day and night. The food was exquisite and I can’t express how amazing the view from the Rooftop Bar was. Would stay here again without a doubt.

We loved our stay at Hotel Marignan Champs-Elysees! We had 2 adjoining rooms, which was great because we were traveling with our 2 children. They had little gifts waiting for them in their room, along. with snacks! What a great personal touch! The location is wonderful, but the BEST part was the hotel staff- they were AMAZING!!!!!!!!!
We will absolutely stay here again when we visit this winter!

Very pleasant stay , excellent location , staff amazing , only little critique the rooms just a little dark.excellent location we walked everywhere and lots of restaurants and bars in walking distance , all the staff are very pleasant.

Given the requirements for a hotel, it was a wise choice. Such as the welcoming atmosphere, the helpful staff, the breakfast, the room service, the location, the lovely panoramic view from the rooftop, and last but not least, the comfortable stay given the hot weather at the time.

very nice hotel
Friendly staff
High level of hygiene

The location of the hotel is very special
Thank you fore every one
The service is very excellent
If I had another chance to visit Paris
I will stay in this same hotel

Brilliant hotel with a fantastic view, great service and ideal location. Staff go above and beyond to help. Thoroughly enjoyed the stay and the view of the Eiffel Tower added that touch of magic. Thanks to all for helping us have such an enjoyable stay and experience. Good value for money. I highly recommend this hotel for a treat trip away.

From arrival staff were so helpful and welcoming. Throughout stay a high standard was kept, room and facilities were second to none. Also the rooftop bar has one of the nicest views of Paris and Eiffel Tower I have seen unbelievable! Amazing stay and will definitely be back, would recommend to anyone if they are looking for a luxury stay.

Thank you all for the great experience, hope to see you again , maybe in few monthes, thanks alot marion , abdualrahman, ahmed , every body, you were a big help to me, i will come again and i will choose this hotel

We stayed for 7 days and were in Paris for the French Open. Easy to get to the Open using the metro trains that were less than 5 min walk front the hotel. Rooms are a bit small from a US perspective, but suited our needs perfectly. Breakfast being included is definitely worth it and the buffet is very good. Staff at the hotel is extremely friendly, helpful and willing to go the extra step when needed. Awesome trip, would stay there again

Excellent location. Great staff. Outstanding service. The size of the junior suite was confortable. Bathroom bigger than expected. Very clean. Nice bar in the roof top with an amazing view to the Eiffel tower.

Best service ever .excellent cleaning. Friendly staff
Very serious about our baby needs
Comfortable rooms . Nice smelling. Tasty food . Excellent location next to avenue Montaigne
We will book this place soon for sure

This Hotel is in the best location in Paris. Front desk staff are friendly and ready to help. The rooftop bar was quite and a great view of the city. Next time I’m in Paris it will be my go to hotel!!

I stayed here with my wife for 4 days and everything from the staff and quality of the hotel exceeded expectations. We did pay extra for a balcony with an amazing view of the Eiffel Tower. Although not officially open yet the roof top terrace is amazing.

The location was perfect, an easy walk to the Eiffel Tower, the louvre, and everywhere really! There’s a train stop at the top do the corner too! But what’s more important is : The service at this hotel is above and beyond. I informed them that it was my wife’s birthday, and they put up individual happy birthday balloons in our room and left a cake! One day, a front desk clerk (Virgil) offered to run out and get me an eclair after noticing I was tired. Another front desk clerk (Vivek) found and reserved us the best restaurants with a front row view to the Eiffel Tower. My wife and I were treated like queens from the moment we went in. And the room was perfect, the staff cleaned our room two or three times a day, and made sure we had only the best! We left them a very large tip to express our gratitude because they consistently went above and beyond.

Rooms don't look like the pictures online, and the lounge was dirty. We wanted to have dinner but not in these conditions.
We left immediately and Checked-out not even an hour after we arrived. We booked 2 rooms and asked for a full refund, but the hotel told us they would charge us the first night and refund the remaining nights we booked. This isn't something i was happy about, and a full refund should've been given.
The remaining nights still haven't been refunded to our travel agent who booked this Hotel for us. I'm disappointed and surprised that this is a 5 Star Hotel. Anyone who wants to book this Hotel should be very carful and should do more research about it.

The only good thing was the Staff's Kindness and Professiolism.

Really enjoyed out stay. The Staff were very friendly and could not do enough for us. The suite was very nice and clean, although we never did master the light switches in the room. All the amenities in the room were great. If I had to fault our stay it would be better lighting in the room.

Hotel Marignan is gorgeous and steeped with ancient history, but alive with modern details. The ambiance was carefully curated, artsy, unique, and beautiful. It was convenient with a metro station at the end of the block and lots of shopping nearby. But it was the people who worked there who really made this place special. At every moment we felt welcomed and well cared for. Going to a foreign country can be intimidating, but the staff at Hotel Marignan went out of their way to make everything easy for us, and they did it with a smile. The hotel restaurant offered delicious dinner and was a great place to stop for a cocktail after a day walking around the city. The breakfast was also exceptional and worth getting with the room. One other super perk with this place was the private movie theater in the basement. We spent many an evening there curled up with blankets on the comfy lounge chairs. All of these things were special, but truly, it was because of the people who worked there that this might have been the best hotel experience we have ever had!

This is an amazing hotel. The location is superb, the atmosphere in the hotel is excellent, the food is excellent, the rooms are all unique and so comfortable and clean, and most of all the staff are the best I have experienced in Paris. So helpful, kind, attentive and informative. Truly amazing.

This hotel far exceeded our expectations.
The staff were excellent, beautiful rooms and and great location.
It will now be my go to place for any Paris trips.
I will be recommending it to all my family and friends.

My daughter and I visited Paris in Spring and stayed at Hotel Marignan Champs-Elysees. We had a wonderful experience. We loved the hotel. It was beautiful and clean and everyone was so pleasant. We had a lovely view of the Eiffel Tower and walked to many of our favorite boutiques from the hotel.

Amazing venue, hotel is extremely luxurious with outstanding service. All the staff were incredibly friendly and attentive. We took our teen kids for the bank holiday. Can’t wait to go back. Would highest recommend.

This hotel and its staff are just incredible. My girlfriend and I could not have been more happy with our stay at the Marignan Champs-Elysees and would absolutely recommend it to others looking for a quaint, chic, cozy, upscale, boutique accommodations in the heart of Paris attractions, restaurants, and shopping.

Let me start with the staff at the hotel. The front desk and concierge (Marion) were so kind and always made us feel welcome and offered great suggestions. Vivek (sorry if I misspelled) the night front desk representative went out of his way to make a list of must see items for us since it was our first time to Paris. Marion helped us with fantastic lunch and dinner recommendations. The doormen were great and always so kind and ready to help us in anyway. The evening doormen even went out of his way to take us up to the top floor to see the Eiffel Tower view at night and helped us capture several of the best pictures of our stay. My sincere thanks to all the great team at the Marignan!! :)

The location was great. It was on a quiet street and within a few minutes of walking to great shopping on the des Champs Ulysses, major attractions, and some really stellar restaurants.

The hotel itself was a great blend of modern chic and cozy. Our room was very nicely appointed, very clean, and well maintained. We just felt right at home and comfortable from the moment with stepped into the room. We did not get a chance to try the attached restaurant and bar, Lemon, but it looked very nice and had a comfortable ambience.

The pricing was fair for what you receive and we definitely felt like the hotel value for the euro was good. Overall, I would absolutely recommend the property to others. Merci to the Marignan team and we will be back soon! Au Revior...

we enjoyed our stay, central location and above all kindly and very helpful staff. we took twice dinner at the bar which was correct int terms of quality/price. the room (junior suite) met our expectation. we go back

Once again our stay with Hotel Marignan Champs-Elysèes lived up to our expectations from previous visits.
The level of service and attention to detail is exceptional. This along with the location keeps us coming back.
Until next time, thanks again Hotel Marignan ❤️

Best hotel we had ever. The service was sublime, the staff are very friendly and english was not a problem. The breakfast was perfect and te cocktails tasty, we will definitally come back. Paris is and will always be a beautifull city 😍

Our stay were enjoyable in March 2022. The hotel staff are very supportive and doing their best to support the guests. The level our service is exceptional. I recommend hotel Marignan for any family staying in Paris.

I chose this hotel for its proximity to shopping at Avenue des Champs-Elysees and Avenue Montaigne and to the Franklin D. Roosevelt Metro station, but what I certainly did not expect was the amazing service from the friendly staff of this hotel. Marion, the front office manager, checked me in and even though I arrived earlier than the check-in time, the room was ready, so she gladly took me on a quick tour of the hotel and also showed me my room. She was very friendly and would always address me by name, and was always willing to answer any questions I had. The rest of the staff also would address me by name, assist me with my bags without even being asked, and would provide housekeeping services twice a day so my room was always fresh .

Some reviews have stated that the hotel has a dark lobby, but I think that adds to the luxurious appeal. The rooms themselves are decorated with light finishes and also have lots of light, and the large windows let in a good amount of natural light as well. It was interesting that the toilet and the shower were in two separate rooms, but I realized later that is somewhat standard in Europe. The bed was plush and comfortable, and the room was spacious and quiet.

But probably the biggest draw of this hotel is its location. Just steps away from fabulous shopping at Avenue Montaigne and the various shops, restaurants, and sights on Avenue des Champs Elysees. Also close by is the Franklin D. Roosevelt Metro station, and with that, you have easy access to the rest of Paris. Other hotels in the area may charge double or triple the rate I paid, yet I still received the same five-star travel experience.

Thank you, Marion, and the rest of the staff at Hotel Marignan for an amazing stay! I'll be sure to recommend this hotel to my friends and family and I hope to return soon!

Thank you once again for the service. See you soon again! The location is perfect, walking distance to almost everything in Paris. The staff is very helpful and the rooms are big and very modern. We are coming back for sure.

We had a great stay here, the roomwas quiet and very comfortable and the hotel stylish. There was a good choice of breakfast foods. What made this place were the staff who were very welcoming throughout.

We stayed 5 nights at Marignan and absolutely loved it! Location was perfect, rooms were clean and the staff were super attentive and helpful. Highly recommend. Thank you for a great stay and see you next time :)

Great stay! Excellent service and friendly staff. Breakfast was excellent and was offered also many gf options. Dinning area was cosy. A bit disappointed for not having access to the terrace during winter time.

Staff are pleasant and helpful. But only one elevator, faulty electronic door lock, noisy pipes that ensure you hear when your neighbor goes to the toilet leaves you wondering. Again, can't fault the staff for trying.. just the feeling they cut corners and budget when they built/renovated it..

Beautiful boutique hotel in the centre of Paris, take a room with a view of the eiffel tower and a balcony, it‘s so romantic!Bathroom with bathtub and shower and extra wc is stunning.I loved the exclusive bed linen.You are welcomed by friendly staff, everything was just fantastic!,,

I cannot rave enough about this place, it is absolutely stunning, classy hotel, beautiful rooms, view of the Eiffel Tower which is worth it’s weight on gold…. But the staff, I have never stayed in a hotel where the staff have looked after us so well we are treated like family. No where else we will stay when we come back to Paris and will tell everyone to come stay here. Thank you so much to Tony, Marion and Jan among others for looking after us. Rosie & Kieran xx

Dear team Marignan, and specifically Marion,

Thank you. Thank you so much for being part of, and organising the best night of my life.

I connected with Marion in early-January, explaining my wish to propose to my girl in the Eiffel suite with a balcony overlooking the tower. She was so helpful. We kept each other in the loop through over 30 e-mails, in which support was offered when it came to the music, the decoration, the photographer and the coordination. It all went according to plan.

The hotel looks amazing as well. Rooms matched the photos and beat all the expectations. And the staff was really friendly and helpful.

From the bottom of our heart, thanks! I wish you all the best and we hope to re-visit you again.

🇫🇷💍❤️

We had the pleasure of experiencing staying at the Suite Marignan Eiffel which absolutely magical! The suite itself is very spacious and elegantly decorated and the best part was the most impressive terracewith unobstructed views of the Eiffel Tower! I highly recommend experiencing staying at Hotel Marignan -staff was kind, friendly but also professional at the same time and the breakfast was delicious!

We had a lovely stay at this hotel. I visited this hotel with my daughter of 16 years old. Our room was incredible beautiful, the hotel service was wonderful. We had an amazing stay in Paris because of the services of Hôtel Marignan Champs Elysées. We really experienced and enjoyed the 5- star services. It really is Parisian refinement.

The location of this hotel is great with many fine restaurants and shops around (L'Avenue at the end of the street was particularly nice). The hotel staff were very accommodating and easy to approach. I used the valet parking and it was a very smooth experience. Our room was very comfortable and clean. The shower is particularly nice.

One minor compliant I have is that the ceiling is kind of low on the non-open ceiling part of the family room. I am 1.99m and I was *just* able to stand up straight.

We just came back from our trip to Paris and I must say that staying at Hotel Marignan was the highlight of our trip! The room was extremely comfortable with stunning views of Eiffel Tower! You have all the luxury you need from the bathtub to heated toilet seats. We especially love the large selection at breakfast! I am such a breakfast person so I really appreciated the feast in the morning! Everybody was so attentive and welcoming that we would love to go back and stay at Hotel Marignan!

We had an amazing stay for our 12-year anniversary !

Every staff member was very nice and we had a very warm welcome from Marion.

We booked the suite with view on the Eiffel Tower, it was wonderful.
The terrace is big and the suite is super nice.
We had dinner at the restaurant and really enjoyed it. The food was very good and the wine too. Our waiter Arabo was lovely.

We visited this hotel two years ago, and since this moment, already started planning our next visit! So we can say that the second time was even better than the first one 😍😍
We were upgraded to a room with an amazing Eiffel tower view, entered the room just to find an amazing cake and lots of french yummy treats!!!! And of course the amazing breakfast and the most helpful staff !!!!!
If you're looking for a place which is more than just a hotel in Paris... You've just found it.
